Slovaquian Jan Svorada claimed the first  stage victory of his career in the Tour of Italy here on Monday.
Russian overall leader Evgueni Berzin retained the pink jersey after the  153km ninth stage.
Svorada, 25, beat Italians Endrio Leoni, winner of the fifth stage, and  Giovanni Fidanza in a sprint.
Uzbek Djamolidin Abdujaparov and Belgian Eric Vanderaerden crashed on the  final bend but both got up to finish.
